SIMPLE: regulation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Regulation
<hw>Reg`u*la"tion</hw> <pr>(-l?"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of regulating, or the state of being regulated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The temper and <qex>regulation</qex> of our own minds.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A rule or order prescribed for management or
government; prescription; a regulating principle; a governing direction;
precept; law; <as>as, the <ex>regulations</ex> of a society or a
school</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Regulation sword</b></col>, <col><b>cap</b></col>,
<col><b>uniform</b></col>, etc.</mcol> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>, <cd>a sword,
cap, uniform, etc., of the kind or quality prescribed by the official
regulations.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- <er>Law</er>; rule; method; principle; order;
precept. See <er>Law</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Regulative</ent>⟦br⟧
